Sonarr is a PVR for Usenet and BitTorrent users. It can monitor multiple RSS feeds for new episodes of your favorite shows and will grab, sort and rename them. It can also be configured to automatically upgrade the quality of files already downloaded when a better quality format becomes available.

It is not recommended to run Sonarr as root. The default user/group is
'sonarr'.
You can either create this user like this:

    # groupadd sonarr
    # useradd -d /var/lib/sonarr -s /bin/false -g sonarr sonarr 

Or you can pass a different user/group if you prefer:

    # RUN_USER=foo RUN_GROUP=bar ./$PRGNAM.SlackBuild

You can have Sonarr start/stop automatically at boot/shutdown. In
/etc/rc.d/rc.local add:

    # Start Sonarr at boot
    if [ -x /etc/rc.d/rc.sonarr ]; then
      /etc/rc.d/rc.sonarr start
    if

And in /etc/rc.d/rc.local_shutdown add:

    # Stop Sonarr at shutdown
    if [ -x /etc/rc.d/rc.sonarr ]; then
      /etc/rc.d/rc.sonarr stop
    if

After installing visit http://localhost:8989 to configure Sonarr.
